Description: Apstrata is a cloud based solution providing MNOs with the opportunity to fully participate in the smartphone ecosystem by becoming

Full Description: Apstrata is a cloud based solution providing MNOs with the opportunity to fully participate in the smartphone ecosystem by becoming suppliers to the App and API economies. We empower MNOs to unlock new business models, differentiate from the competition and create new revenue streams. The smartphone re-launch in 2007 completely disrupted the traditional mobile network operator (MNO) business model.  All value added potential including core services such as voice and messaging has moved or is moving away fast from the network and into apps. This is commoditizing the MNOs business into a bit-pipe and threatening their position as leading consumer brands. By offering the white-labeled Apstrata solution, MNOs enable developers to innovate and monetize Apps and businesses to create & monetize mobile and web-services channels gaining time to market, cost-efficiency and generating revenues faster. We also help the operator to tap into major sources of revenue locked inside their network by opening up their operator billing, messaging, location and user information services through APIs.

Full Description: Portland Bitters Project (PBP) was born in Autumn, 2013.  Since then, we've been hard at work creating cocktail bitters and herbal tinctures.  You can send us a note anytime at pdxbittersproject@gmail.com. Bitters.  What does that really mean?  It all starts with organic, therapeutic-grade botanicals (roots, leaves, fruit, sometimes seeds!).  These are immersed in over-proof spirits and allowed to steep until all their goodness is infused in the liquid.  The botanicals are then strained out, and we're left with tinctures, which are blended together in small batches.  Raw cane sugar is added to round out the flavor on the palate.  Now, magic can happen with a drop or a dash.  Cocktails are a natural direction, and just a little soda water is a refreshing vehicle.  Explore our recipe page for other inspirations (even culinary uses like PBP Swanky Nuts). We house our bitters in amber glass bottles to protect from light and prolong their long life.  The dropper top is perfect for adding just the right amount.  Many commercial bitters include thickeners, artificial coloring and additives.  Our bitters are free from that nonsense to better deliver clean and lively flavor right where it counts.
